            "headline": "Advisors conflicted on crypto, 62% against, 85% say views changed under Trump, with 79% saying role is managing risk.",
            "id": "8aa37ea4-183f-4186-82dc-65311506377f",
            "is_major": true,
            "source": "Benzinga",
            "source_type": "news",
            "summary": "A recent survey conducted by CoinShares indicates that financial advisors are facing a dilemma regarding cryptocurrencies due to the increasing popularity of digital assets and the new administration's favorable stance. The survey shows that 62% of advisors feel conflicted as recommending Bitcoin and other cryptocurrencies may contradict their fiduciary responsibilities, with half fearing that doing so may negatively impact their professional reputation. However, 85% of advisors note a shift in their firms' perspectives on digital assets post the re-election of President Donald Trump, and 79% agree that managing the risks associated with clients investing in cryptocurrencies is now a crucial part of their role. With an increasing number of clients entering the cryptocurrency market, advisors feel the need for more extensive information and education to navigate these complexities effectively.",
            "tickers": [],
            "time": "17:04:22",
            "timestamp": "2025-02-23T17:04:22Z",
            "url": "https://www.benzinga.com/personal-finance/financial-advisors/25/02/43903229/advisors-remain-divided-on-crypto-but-sec-approvals-demand-are-shifting-views"
        },
